nits to reduce java clutter:
{code}
for (Iterator<ImmutablePair<Operator<? extends OperatorDesc>, Operator<? extends OperatorDesc>>> iterator =
value.iterator(); iterator.hasNext();) {
ImmutablePair<Operator<? extends OperatorDesc>, Operator<? extends OperatorDesc>> swap =
iterator.next(); 
{code}
can be replaced with generic forloop which effectively compiles to iterator. 

Also, right hand side types for 'delayedFixups' and 'value' can be replaced with <> (inferred from lhs). 

Both nits can be updated on commit. +1, pending tests.
